
Question_03: Student Details Injection System

Project Explanation

This Spring Core application demonstrates how to inject external configuration values into a bean using @Value. 
Student details like ID, name, and course are stored in a properties file and automatically injected into the Student class. 
This avoids hardcoding values inside the program and makes the application flexible.

Concept:

External configuration using application.properties
Dependency injection using @Value
Loose coupling between code and data

Fields
------
studentId
studentName
course

Operations
-----------
Read values from properties file
Inject values into bean
Display student details